-- Japan Considers Boosting Ground Troops by 13,000 to 168,000, Kyodo Reports
-- Masumi Suga
-- 2010-09-20T04:14:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/japan-considers-boosting-ground-troops-by-13-000-to-168-000-kyodo-reports.html

          
          
             Japanâ€™s  Defense Ministry  is
considering increasing the number of its ground forces by 13,000
to 168,000 soldiers, the first expansion in 38 years, to cope
with challenges including the security situation in East Asia,
Kyodo News reported.  
 The plan may be incorporated in a new national defense
program to be implemented in the fiscal year ending March 2012,
Kyodo  said , citing unnamed people in the ministry and the Self-
Defense Forces.  
 The troop expansion is aimed at coping with the fluid
security situation in East Asia, international terrorism and
natural disasters, according to the report.  
